Hemoglobin-haptoglobin utilization protein B precursor.
"Molecular characterization of hpuAB, the haemoglobin-haptoglobin-
utilization operon of Neisseria meningitidis.";
-!- FUNCTION: Acts as a receptor for hemoglobin or the
    hemoglobin/haptoglobin complex and is required for heme uptake.
-!- SUBCELLULAR LOCATION: Cell outer membrane; peripheral membrane
    protein (Potential).
-!- SIMILARITY: Belongs to the tonB-dependent receptor family.
Membrane; Outer membrane; Receptor; Signal; TonB box; Transport.
